  "commentary": "With SPX at 7101 sitting right between the negative gamma pockets at 7115 (-5.1B) and 7110 (-3.9B), dealers are currently in buy mode as they're short gamma in this zone, creating upward pressure. However, the strong positive gamma wall at 7100 (+4.7B) below and massive resistance at 7150 (+6.0B) and 7200 (+7.5B) above should contain the move and promote mean reversion back toward the 7100-7115 range. Watch for rejection at 7115 as dealers flip from buying to selling, with the 7150 level acting as a significant magnet given the large positive gamma concentration.\n\nBottom line: expect choppy action between 7100-7115 with upside capped near 7150.",
